            <abstract id="ref2" label="Abstract">This collection details Edward Bartek’s experiences in the Pacific during World War II. The collection contains video of oral history interview, journals, photographs. The materials provide information on various military engagements in the Pacific from Kiska to New South Wales. Along with evidence of U.S. military moral and courage the collection brings to light the impact of war related stress and isolation on military personnel.</abstract>
            <physloc id="ref8" label="Location">Center for Public Policy and Social Research (CPPSR) 207 DiLoreto Hall, Central Connecticut State University (CCSU) 1615 Stanley St. New Britain, CT 06050</physloc>
