            </origination>
        </did>
        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Edward Bartek enlisted in the United States Navy in 1939 to see the world. Receiving his basic training in Rhode Island he subsequently was assigned to the U.S.S. Quincy in Norfolk, Virginia. After seventeen days aboard the U.S.S. Quincy, Edward was transferred to the U.S.S. Ranger, an aircraft carrier which was sent to Guantanamo Bay for maneuvers. Edward served as an Electrician’s Mate aboard the U.S.S. Ranger as it patrolled the Atlantic in search of German submarines. After serving two and a half years on the U.S.S. Ranger Edward was assigned to the destroyer, the U.S.S. Beale as the Electrician’s Mate 1st Class. Supervising 13 other electricians on the U.S.S. Beale, Edward took part in eleven invasions, two sea battles, numerous air attacks, shore bombardments and convoys.</p>
        </bioghist>
